onment component is defined to include the following activities: \u2022 Harmonize HIV policies with laws that impede the response. \u2022 Reduce harassment, violence, and stigma. \u2022 Ensure continuity and consistency of programmes and services. \u2022 Support MSM and transgender community-based organizations and NGOs. \u2022 Remove structural barriers", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "fb9616f5-f4de-4a2e-8de5-446c52fb92d4": {"__data__": {"id_": "fb9616f5-f4de-4a2e-8de5-446c52fb92d4", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/hiv-and-law-south-east-asia", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "HIV and the Law in South-East Asia", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/hiv-and-law-south-east-asia", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "db5de37211f34d672a18a2b666c0a201d2f5b4f244483c3a5b097891c20ca6c0"}, "3": {"node_id": "4363c0e2-ebcf-40d0-a6ab-00c255ac324f", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/hiv-and-law-south-east-asia", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "6eaf0174a05892f775670f9cea375e0d484b2204511407d18639afb3e1fdad62"}}, "hash": "4f16c39e592d9074c8dae484726b66d1a909b9df332fc448a768a35e07e5d4c1", "text": "to the use of services by MSM and transgender people. \u2022 Address transgender issues, such as the ability to change one\u2019s name and gender identity in official documents, and the