CTIVE LEgISLATION 9.3.3 Lao PDR Law on HIV/AIDS Control and Prevention (2010) Article 51 Prohibitions for health service providers Health service providers are prohibited from taking a blood test for HIV without consent from the concerned individual, except for cases required by law. 9.3.4 Philippines Philippines AIDS Prevention and Control Act 1998 (RA 8504) Section 15 Consent as a requisite for HIV testing No compulsory HIV testing shall be allowed, however, the State shall encourage voluntary testing for individuals with a high risk for contracting HIV: Provided that written informed consent must first be obtained. Such consent shall be obtained from the person concerned if he/she is of legal age or from the parents or legal guardian in the case of a minor or a mentally incapacitated individual. Lawful consent to HIV testing of a donated human body, organ, tissue, or blood shall be considered as having been given when: a a person volunteers or freely agrees to donate his/her blood, organ, or tissue for transfusion, transplantation, or research; b a person has executed a legacy in accordance with Section 3 of Republic Act No. 7170, also known as the \u201cOrgan Donation Act of 1991\u201d; c a donation is executed in accordance with Section 4 of Republic Act No. 7170.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "fe2bd385-ccae-41d1-9471-0032b0db1ad5": {"__data__": {"id_": "fe2bd385-ccae-41d1-9471-0032b0db1ad5", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/hiv-and-law-south-east-asia", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "HIV and the Law in South-East Asia", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_